Definition: a specialized condensed region of each chromosome that appears during mitosis where the chromatids are held together to form an X shape
Example: the centromere is difficult to sequence
Synonyms: adj, pert, centromeric, kinetochore, structure, chromosome, p, a, specialized, condensed, region, of, each, that, appears, during, mitosis, where, the, chromatids, are, held, together, to, form, an, X, shape, is, difficult, sequence
Category: noun.body
